<h2 id="how-to-access">How to access the Figma UI Kit</h2>
<p>There are <strong>three ways</strong> to use the NSW Design System in Figma. The right option for you depends on how you need to interact with the library:</p>

<ol>
  <li><strong>General access (View-only)</strong> - Anyone can access the <a href="https://www.figma.com/file/PVrERKnckLTlJSPk12gbtS/NSW-Digital-Design-System?node-id=18830%3A13437" target="_blank">Figma UI Kit</a> in view-only mode. This allows users to browse the library but does not allow inspecting components or copying assets into projects.</li>
  
  <li><strong>Inspect access</strong> - Users who require the ability to inspect components (for specifications, styles, and measurements) should request access by emailing <a href="mailto:digital@customerservice.nsw.gov.au">digital@customerservice.nsw.gov.au</a>.</li>

  <li><strong>Offline Figma library extension (Most comprehensive)</strong> - Users who need to integrate the NSW Design System library into their Figma projects must request access to the <i>**static, offline version**</i> of the UI Kit. <strong>This version will not receive automatic updates.</strong></li>
</ol>

<h3>Option 1: General access (View-only)</h3>
<p>Anyone can access the UI Kit without signing in to a Figma account. However, this method does not allow component inspection or copying elements into other files.</p>

<p><strong>Access the View-only NSW Design System UI Kit:</strong>  
<a href="https://www.figma.com/file/PVrERKnckLTlJSPk12gbtS/NSW-Digital-Design-System?node-id=18830%3A13437" target="_blank">View the Figma UI Kit</a></p>

<h3>Option 2: Inspect access</h3>
<p>If you need to inspect elements (for development handoff or style details), request access by emailing:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:digital@customerservice.nsw.gov.au">digital@customerservice.nsw.gov.au</a></li>
</ul>

<h3>Option 3: Offline Figma library extension</h3>
<p>If your Figma team is separate from the Digital NSW team and you need to integrate the NSW Design System as a Figma library, a static offline version is available. You will need to manually add this version as a local library.</p>

<p><strong>Request Access:</strong></p>
<p>To receive the latest version of the NSW Digital Design System offline file, email:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:digital@customerservice.nsw.gov.au">digital@customerservice.nsw.gov.au</a></li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Steps to install once received:</strong></p>
<ol>
  <li>Download the <code>.fig</code> file provided by the NSW Digital Team.</li>
  <li>Open Figma and go to <strong>File</strong> → <strong>Import</strong>.</li>
  <li>Select the downloaded <code>.fig</code> file and import it into your organisation’s workspace.</li>
  <li>Once imported, enable it as a library:
    <ul>
      <li>Go to <strong>Assets</strong> → <strong>Library</strong> and toggle it on.</li>
      <li>Ensure your team has the correct permissions to access the file.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ol>

<h2 id="version-updates">Version updates</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Inspect Access users will always see the latest version.</li>
  <li>Offline Library users should check the <a href="https://github.com/digitalnsw/nsw-design-system" target="_blank">GitHub repository</a> for updates and manually request new versions.</li>
</ul>

<h2 id="getting-started">Getting started with Figma</h2>
<p>If you're new to Figma, we recommend starting with their beginner-friendly course: <a href="https://help.figma.com/hc/en-us/sections/30880632542743" target="_blank">Figma Design for Beginners</a>.</p>

<h2 id="sharing-file">Sharing the file</h2>
<ol>
  <li>From your Figma dashboard, select the <strong>NSW Design System</strong> project in the left-hand panel. <em>(Do not share from within the file itself, as this will limit access.)</em></li>
  <li>Click <strong>Share</strong> in the top-right corner.</li>
  <li>Enter the email addresses of your team members.</li>
</ol>

<p>For those who only need to <strong>view</strong> the UI Kit, use the <a href="https://www.figma.com/file/PVrERKnckLTlJSPk12gbtS/NSW-Digital-Design-System?node-id=18830%3A13437" target="_blank">View-Only Design System Figma UI Kit</a>.</p>

